   <body>
      <section>
         <ol>
            <li>Log off the obop account (using the sequence Start-&gt;Shutdown-&gt;Log Off).</li>
            <li>Log onto the Machine Server with the administrator account (password: scsgolden).</li>
            <li id="li_n2g_rnz_qzb">Trigger the scheduled tasks.<note id="note_bkx_4nz_qzb">
                  <p>This step is for Windows Server 2003 systems only. If using Windows Server 2008
                     (SCS-0716 GR04 or greater), use step <xref href="#r20B23C2-BB02-11F0-7096-09173F13E4C5/li_g2r_qnz_qzb">4</xref> instead.</p>
               </note>
               <ol id="ol_o2g_rnz_qzb">
                  <li>Navigate to the Control Panel (Start -&gt; Settings -&gt; Control Panel or see
                     Figure <xref href="#r20B23C2-BB02-11F0-7096-09173F13E4C5/fig_zsz_1nz_qzb">1</xref> below). <fig id="fig_zsz_1nz_qzb">
                        <title>Figure 1: Navigating to the Control Panel (Windows Server 2003
                           Systems)</title>
                        <image href="media/image1.jpg"
                               placement="break"
                               id="image_atz_1nz_qzb"
                               align="center"/>
                     </fig>
                  </li>
                  <li>Locate the Scheduled Tasks control and double-click it (see Figure <xref href="#r20B23C2-BB02-11F0-7096-09173F13E4C5/fig_c2v_cnz_qzb">2</xref>). <fig id="fig_c2v_cnz_qzb">
                        <title>Figure 2: Scheduled Tasks Control (Windows Server 2003)</title>
                        <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                               placement="break"
                               id="image_d2v_cnz_qzb"
                               align="center"/>
                     </fig>
                  </li>
                  <li>The scheduled tasks will now be displayed. Right-click each of the following
                     scheduled tasks (in order), and then select Run: <ol id="ol_p2g_rnz_qzb">
                        <li>DBBackup.</li>
                        <li>DBMonitorBackup.</li>
                        <li>BackupFiles <note id="note_q2g_rnz_qzb">
                              <p>Wait for the system to stop displaying the message “Running”
                                 prior to moving onto the next one. (See Figure <xref href="#r20B23C2-BB02-11F0-7096-09173F13E4C5/fig_mpf_lnz_qzb">3</xref> for an example of a
                                 running scheduled task).</p>
                           </note>
                           <fig id="fig_mpf_lnz_qzb">
                              <title>Figure 3: Scheduled Tasks Window</title>
                              <p>
                                 <i>(Note that the DBBackup Task is Currently
                                 Running)</i>
                              </p>
                              <image href="media/image3.jpg"
                                     placement="break"
                                     id="image_qpf_lnz_qzb"
                                     align="center"/>
                           </fig>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li>When the BackupFiles scheduled task is complete, the backup will have been
                     copied to the backup server.</li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li id="li_g2r_qnz_qzb">Trigger the scheduled tasks. This step is for Windows Server 2008
               systems only. If using Windows Server 2003 (SCS-0716 GR03 or prior), use step <xref href="#r20B23C2-BB02-11F0-7096-09173F13E4C5/li_n2g_rnz_qzb">3</xref> instead. <ol id="ol_h2r_qnz_qzb">
                  <li>Open the Server Manager by clicking on the <uicontrol>Start</uicontrol> Menu,
                     then right-clicking the <uicontrol>Computer</uicontrol> icon, and then
                     selecting Manage (see Figure <xref href="#r20B23C2-BB02-11F0-7096-09173F13E4C5/fig_r5t_lnz_qzb">4</xref>). <fig id="fig_r5t_lnz_qzb">
                        <title>Figure 4: Opening Server Manager (Windows Server 2008)</title>
                        <image href="media/image4.jpg"
                               placement="break"
                               id="image_s5t_lnz_qzb"
                               align="center"/>
                     </fig>
                  </li>
                  <li>When Server Manager opens, navigate to the task scheduler library as shown in
                     Figure <xref href="#r20B23C2-BB02-11F0-7096-09173F13E4C5/fig_elf_nnz_qzb">5</xref>. <fig id="fig_elf_nnz_qzb">
                        <title>Figure 5: Scheduled Tasks (WindowsServer 2008) DBBackup
                           Running</title>
                        <image href="media/image5.jpg"
                               placement="break"
                               id="image_flf_nnz_qzb"
                               align="center"/>
                     </fig>
                  </li>
                  <li>The scheduled tasks will now be displayed. Right-click each of the following
                     scheduled tasks (in order) and then select “Run.” <ol id="ol_i2r_qnz_qzb">
                        <li>DBBackup</li>
                        <li>DBMonitorBackup</li>
                        <li>BackupFiles <note id="note_j2r_qnz_qzb">
                              <p>Wait for the system to stop displaying the message “
                                 Running” prior to moving onto the next task. With Windows
                                 Server 2008, the task status does not automatically refresh, and
                                 the <uicontrol>F5</uicontrol> key must be pressed to refresh the
                                 task status.</p>
                           </note>
                           <note id="note_k2r_qnz_qzb">
                              <p>See Figure <xref href="#r20B23C2-BB02-11F0-7096-09173F13E4C5/fig_elf_nnz_qzb">5</xref> for an
                                 example of a running scheduled task </p>
                           </note>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li>When the BackupFiles scheduled task is complete, the backup will have been
                     copied to the backup server. </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li>Follow the instructions in FES-03-117 <i>Verifying Machine Server Backups</i> to validate that the backup worked correctly</li>
         </ol>
      </section>
